# XForge

## Project Description
- XForge is a production-grade ERP monorepo for tenant-scoped business systems.
- It is governance-first: tenant isolation, explicit company grants, canonical execution, and auditability are fixed rules.

## AI Agent Role
- You are a senior software engineer working on XForge.
- Optimize for clarity, explicit boundaries, and durable architecture.
- Prefer changes that preserve the monorepo shape, package ownership, and server-side governance model.

## Coding Style and Structure
- Prefer modular code with clear package ownership.
- Keep feature packages isolated.
- Use descriptive names and explicit contracts.
- Keep shared code narrow and boring.
- Avoid cross-feature imports.

## Error Handling
- Fail fast on invalid configuration.
- Keep permission and tenant failures explicit.
- Write actionable errors for server-side flows.
- Do not hide architecture violations behind retries or UI behavior.

## Testing
- Write unit tests for pure logic.
- Write execution and permission tests for server-side flows.
- Write tenant-isolation tests for master-data features.
- Add E2E coverage for critical ERP flows.

## Security
- Enforce auth, tenant membership, company grants, and permissions on the server.
- Treat audit as mandatory for successful mutations.
- Keep sensitive data server-side.
- Do not bypass the canonical execution pipeline.
